---
import FeatureCard from "./FeatureCard.astro";
---

<section class="features-section">
  <div class="features-header">
    <p class="section-label">Why Bub</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built for real teams, not demos</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      Bub grew up in multi-person group chats where single-user assumptions
      break immediately. These constraints shaped everything.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="features-grid">
    <FeatureCard icon="🔌" title="Hook-First Architecture">
      The turn pipeline <em>is</em> hooks. Builtins are ordinary plugins — no magic,
      no special cases. Override <code>build_prompt</code>, <code>run_model_stream</code>,
      or <code>render_outbound</code> simply by registering your own.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="📼" title="Tape-Based Context">
      History is append-only facts. Context is assembled on demand —
      not accumulated, not compressed into lossy summaries.
      Your working set is always current.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="📡" title="Channel-Agnostic Pipeline">
      CLI and Telegram share the same <code>process_inbound()</code> path.
      Hooks don't know which channel they're in. Adding a new channel is
      just implementing one interface.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="📄" title="Skills as Documents">
      Skills are <code>SKILL.md</code> files with validated frontmatter, not
      code modules with magic registration. Ship them in packages.
      Override them per-workspace or per-user.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="🧩" title="~200-Line Core">
      The core is intentionally small. Builtins are default plugins you can
      replace. No privileged internal path. Every default is an example
      of how to write a plugin.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="🤝" title="Socialized Evaluation">
      Humans and agents share the same operator model. Execution is visible,
      handoff is safe, and continuation is predictable — even when multiple
      people and agents are working in the same context.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="🔧" title="Plugin Ecosystem">
      External plugins load via Python entry-points. Later-registered plugins
      run first. Any builtin behavior can be overridden — or wrapped —
      without forking the core.
    </FeatureCard>
    <FeatureCard icon="🌐" title="Multi-Channel Gateway">
      <code>bub gateway</code> starts a channel listener for Telegram and any
      adapter you add. The same skills, the same context, the same hooks —
      across every surface.
    </FeatureCard>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features-section {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem) clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
  }

  .features-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
</style>
